                    {
                      "text": "Homemade pizza is a fantastic budget-friendly meal! You can make a delicious, classic Margherita-style pizza for a fraction of the cost of delivery.\n\nHere is a simple, affordable recipe:\n\n### **Budget-Friendly Homemade Pizza**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n*   **Dough:** 2 \u00bd cups all-purpose flour, 1 packet instant yeast (or 2 \u00bc tsp), 1 tsp salt, 1 tsp sugar, 1 cup warm water, 1 tbsp olive oil.\n*   **Sauce:** 1 small can (8 oz) tomato sauce, 1 tsp dried oregano, \u00bd tsp garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.\n*   **Toppings:** 8 oz shredded mozzarella cheese.\n\n**Instructions:**\n1.  **Dough:** Mix flour, yeast, salt, and sugar in a bowl. Add warm water and oil. Stir until a ball forms, then knead on a floured surface for 5 minutes. Let it rest for 15-20 minutes.\n2.  **Prep:** Preheat your oven to 425\u00b0F (220\u00b0C).\n3.  **Assemble:** Roll or stretch the dough onto a baking sheet or pizza pan. Spread the mixed sauce, then sprinkle with cheese.\n4.  **Bake:** Bake for 12\u201315 minutes until the crust is golden and the cheese is bubbly.\n\n**Cost-saving tip:** Buy generic/store-brand flour and canned tomato sauce\u2014they work just as well as name brands for pizza!\n\nDoes this sound like something you'd like to try, or would you like to add some specific toppings? If you're happy with this, I can finalize it and get your shopping list ready!"
